    "comment": "Rationale: Impairment of synaptic vesicle recycling was detected by measuring FM4-64FX uptake in neurons transfected with mutant but not wild type forms of Rab27b.\n\nLiteral excerpt: \"Interestingly, we found that both GTP- and GDP-preferring Rab27b mutants profoundly impair stimulus-dependent recycling of SVs. Similar effects have been observed using functionally equivalent mutants of other Rab GTPases, including the closely related Rab3 proteins (Schlüter et al., 2002; Star et al., 2005).\". Experimental description: Sequencing of cDNA encoded by plasmid. Not mentioned in the paper.\n\n19/01/2017 Pim\nNote: please note that the expert that created this annotation is part of the lab that created this publication. The species information is therefore derived from direct communication with the authors.\n\n2/3/2017 Pim\nThe functional studies in Fig.7 use a OE protein. Author reports a rat species for this copnstruct.",
